article.headline: Siena 77, Fordham 59
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Michael Haddix scored 17 points and grabbed six rebounds to lead Siena to a 77-59 win over Fordham Tuesday night. Siena (2-0) dominated the boards, outrebounding Fordham 61-31. Justin Miller led the Saints in rebounds with 11. Fordham jumped out to a 13-6 lead in the game's first five minutes, but Siena went on a 9-0 run over the next 6 1/2 minutes to take the lead. Siena led by eight at the half, but Fordham closed the gap to 45-40 in the second half. The Saints responded with a 12-0 run to take a commanding 57-40 lead and cruised to the win. Fordham (0-2) hit just 5 of 22 three-point tries and shot 38.3 percent from the field. Siena hit 6 of 15 threes and shot 41.4 percent. Michael Haynes scored 20 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Fordham. Mark Jarrell-Wright added 14 points and seven rebounds.
